# Hint: Use input() to get numbers and operator
# Use conditional statements to perform the correct operation
def calculator():
    pass  # Replace with your implementation

# Uncomment to test your function
# calculator()`} 
                />
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-300">Solution Hints</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                  <li>Use <code>float(input())</code> to get numeric inputs</li>
                  <li>Use conditional statements (<code>if</code>/<code>elif</code>) to handle different operators</li>
                  <li>Handle potential division by zero</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </li>
            
            <li>
              <strong>Age Verification:</strong> Write a program that checks if a person is eligible to vote (age >= 18) and is a citizen.
              <div class="mt-4">
                <CodePlayground 
                  client:load 
                  initialCode={`# Age Verification Challenge
# TODO: Create a function to check voting eligibility
# Hint: Use logical operators to combine conditions
def vote_eligibility():
    pass  # Replace with your implementation

# Uncomment to test your function
# vote_eligibility()`} 
                />
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-300">Solution Hints</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                  <li>Use <code>input()</code> to get age and citizenship status</li>
                  <li>Use the <code>and</code> operator to check multiple conditions</li>
                  <li>Convert age to an integer for comparison</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </li>
            
            <li>
              <strong>Temperature Converter:</strong> Use operators to convert Celsius to Fahrenheit and vice versa.
              <div class="mt-4">
                <CodePlayground 
                  client:load 
                  initialCode={`# Temperature Conversion Challenge
# TODO: Create a function to convert temperatures
# Hint: Use mathematical operators for conversion formulas
def temperature_converter():
    pass  # Replace with your implementation

# Uncomment to test your function
# temperature_converter()`} 
                />
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-300">Solution Hints</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                  <li>Celsius to Fahrenheit: <code>(C * 9/5) + 32</code></li>
                  <li>Fahrenheit to Celsius: <code>(F - 32) * 5/9</code></li>
                  <li>Use <code>input()</code> to get temperature and scale</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Practice Problem Solutions</h2>
        <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Detailed Solutions</h3>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">1. Calculator Challenge Solution</h4>
              <CodePlayground 
                client:load 
                initialCode={`# Solution 1: Calculator Challenge
def calculator():
    # Get user inputs
    num1 = float(input("Enter first number: "))
    num2 = float(input("Enter second number: "))
    operator = input("Enter operator (+, -, *, /, %): ")
    
    # Perform calculation based on operator
    if operator == '+':
        result = num1 + num2
    elif operator == '-':
        result = num1 - num2
    elif operator == '*':
        result = num1 * num2
    elif operator == '/':
        # Handle division by zero
        result = num1 / num2 if num2 != 0 else "Error: Division by zero"
    elif operator == '%':
        result = num1 % num2
    else:
        result = "Invalid operator"
    
    print(f"Result: {result}")

# Uncomment to test
# calculator()`} 
              />
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">2. Age Verification Solution</h4>
              <CodePlayground 
                client:load 
                initialCode={`# Solution 2: Age Verification
def vote_eligibility():
    age = int(input("Enter your age: "))
    is_citizen = input("Are you a citizen? (yes/no): ").lower() == 'yes'
    
    # Check voting eligibility
    can_vote = age >= 18 and is_citizen
    
    if can_vote:
        print("You are eligible to vote!")
    else:
        print("Sorry, you cannot vote.")

# Uncomment to test
# vote_eligibility()`} 
              />
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">3. Temperature Converter Solution</h4>
              <CodePlayground 
                client:load 
                initialCode={`# Solution 3: Temperature Converter
def temperature_converter():
    choice = input("Convert (C)elsius to Fahrenheit or (F)ahrenheit to Celsius? ").upper()
    
    if choice == 'C':
        celsius = float(input("Enter temperature in Celsius: "))
        fahrenheit = (celsius * 9/5) + 32
        print(f"{celsius}째C is equal to {fahrenheit}째F")
    elif choice == 'F':
        fahrenheit = float(input("Enter temperature in Fahrenheit: "))
        celsius = (fahrenheit - 32) * 5/9
        print(f"{fahrenheit}째F is equal to {celsius}째C")
    else:
        print("Invalid choice")

# Uncomment to test
# temperature_converter()`} 
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>

